1
00:00:06,750 --> 00:00:09,836
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

2
00:00:09,836 --> 00:00:14,007
<i>♪ ♪</i>

3
00:00:14,007 --> 00:00:16,051
‐ He was so brave.

4
00:00:16,051 --> 00:00:17,385
‐ [sighs]

5
00:00:17,385 --> 00:00:20,388
[thunder rumbling]

6
00:00:20,388 --> 00:00:27,437
<i>♪ ♪</i>

7
00:00:31,149 --> 00:00:33,526
PROME: Lecty has
discovered the truth.

8
00:00:33,526 --> 00:00:35,904
The Golden Tribe
did not abandon us

9
00:00:35,904 --> 00:00:37,864
as we, in our grief, believed.

10
00:00:37,864 --> 00:00:40,951
But as was prophesied,
in their infinite wisdom,

11
00:00:40,951 --> 00:00:43,286
they left us the means
to follow them.

12
00:00:43,286 --> 00:00:47,791
They are calling to us
once again.

13
00:00:47,791 --> 00:00:50,251
My friends,
the time has come

14
00:00:50,251 --> 00:00:52,587
for us to cross a new threshold.

15
00:00:52,587 --> 00:00:55,465
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16
00:00:55,465 --> 00:00:58,551
[engines whirring]

17
00:00:59,928 --> 00:01:01,763
NILVAL: [gasps]

18
00:01:01,763 --> 00:01:03,264
It's the "Athalia."

19
00:01:03,264 --> 00:01:06,601
I'll be damned.
They survived.

20
00:01:06,601 --> 00:01:09,646
[engines firing]

21
00:01:10,647 --> 00:01:12,190
‐ Those are enemy ships.

22
00:01:12,190 --> 00:01:13,358
Dozens of them.

23
00:01:13,358 --> 00:01:14,818
‐ Maintain the formation.

24
00:01:14,818 --> 00:01:18,113
They are not to be engaged.

25
00:01:19,948 --> 00:01:21,783
MAN: Our data has confirmed
their ships

26
00:01:21,783 --> 00:01:23,243
are following a Starway,

27
00:01:23,243 --> 00:01:26,079
but it's not one
we have in our records.

28
00:01:26,079 --> 00:01:27,747
NILVAL: The "Argonaut."

29
00:01:27,747 --> 00:01:29,207
No matter where they go,

30
00:01:29,207 --> 00:01:33,461
they leave a trail that's
impossible to miss.

31
00:01:33,461 --> 00:01:35,130
‐ What should we do, Commander?

32
00:01:35,130 --> 00:01:37,882
‐ Reorganize the fleets
in our current zone.

33
00:01:37,882 --> 00:01:40,802
Have one fall back to escort
the "Athalia"

34
00:01:40,802 --> 00:01:42,637
while the rest of us push ahead.

35
00:01:42,637 --> 00:01:44,389
I have faith in the princess.

36
00:01:44,389 --> 00:01:46,433
Let's see where she leads us.

37
00:01:46,433 --> 00:01:49,436
<i>["Gravitation" by Angela]</i>

38
00:01:49,436 --> 00:01:52,522
[woman singing in Japanese]

39
00:01:52,522 --> 00:01:59,529
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40
00:03:24,864 --> 00:03:27,742
[electric flickering]

41
00:03:27,742 --> 00:03:30,829
WOMAN: Emergency backup system
successfully initiated.

42
00:03:30,829 --> 00:03:33,289
Communications,
sub‐engine functionality,

43
00:03:33,289 --> 00:03:35,208
and main sector‐‐
WOMAN: Returning to normal

44
00:03:35,208 --> 00:03:36,543
system control parameters.

45
00:03:36,543 --> 00:03:38,336
‐ As soon as AI
is up and running,

46
00:03:38,336 --> 00:03:40,088
have it initiate recovery.

47
00:03:40,088 --> 00:03:42,048
But recalibrate the data.

48
00:03:42,048 --> 00:03:44,676
Our friend here heals fast.

49
00:03:44,676 --> 00:03:46,886
‐ The system is not
functioning, Master!

50
00:03:46,886 --> 00:03:49,097
The "Argonaut" cannot maintain
sufficient power‐‐

51
00:03:49,097 --> 00:03:52,225
‐ We avoided a crash.

52
00:03:52,225 --> 00:03:53,643
‐ Huh?

53
00:03:53,643 --> 00:03:54,602
‐ Hmm.

54
00:03:54,602 --> 00:03:57,272
We're safe, thanks to you, Bee.

55
00:03:57,272 --> 00:03:58,439
‐ Oh.

56
00:03:58,439 --> 00:04:01,067
Master, inconsistencies
detected.

57
00:04:01,067 --> 00:04:04,445
Data recovery in progress.

58
00:04:06,281 --> 00:04:08,116
A singularity seems
to have occurred

59
00:04:08,116 --> 00:04:09,868
in the area under
renovation, sir.

60
00:04:09,868 --> 00:04:14,330
‐ [chuckles] We're recruited a
new structural engineer.

61
00:04:14,330 --> 00:04:16,708
ALL: [muttering]

62
00:04:24,257 --> 00:04:25,675
‐ Nice work, huh?

63
00:04:25,675 --> 00:04:28,636
And he can manage it all
without raw materials.

64
00:04:28,636 --> 00:04:30,847
‐ I will assist you
in rebuilding your ship

65
00:04:30,847 --> 00:04:33,391
in accordance with the wishes
of the Silver Tribe.

66
00:04:33,391 --> 00:04:36,519
But with all due respect,
how do you manage?

67
00:04:36,519 --> 00:04:38,563
This technology is so primitive.

68
00:04:38,563 --> 00:04:40,940
‐ Well, I'll be damned.
I just realized.

69
00:04:40,940 --> 00:04:42,525
You're the son of a gun
who chased us

70
00:04:42,525 --> 00:04:44,360
off planet Olone, right?

71
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:46,321
Well, isn't that irony for you.

72
00:04:46,321 --> 00:04:49,741
I apologize for the state of our
technology, old friend.

73
00:04:49,741 --> 00:04:52,035
But I'm confident that
you can make due.

74
00:04:52,035 --> 00:04:57,415
‐ I'm able to rebuild as capably
as I can annihilate.

75
00:04:57,415 --> 00:04:59,834
‐ More renovations
confirmed, Master.

76
00:04:59,834 --> 00:05:01,878
He's too fast for me to keep up.

77
00:05:01,878 --> 00:05:03,713
‐ At this rate,
it seems as though

78
00:05:03,713 --> 00:05:06,966
we'll be able to fly out of here
on our own in no time.

79
00:05:06,966 --> 00:05:09,636
But of course,
we still can't give Age

80
00:05:09,636 --> 00:05:12,513
the memorial service
he deserves.

81
00:05:16,517 --> 00:05:18,561
YUTY: He has cut himself off.

82
00:05:18,561 --> 00:05:20,355
No one can read his thoughts.

83
00:05:20,355 --> 00:05:22,565
He won't even respond
to the sound of my voice.

84
00:05:22,565 --> 00:05:25,944
KARKINOS: Leave him be.
It is only fitting.

85
00:05:25,944 --> 00:05:28,071
YUTY: His actions have
condemned me to feel

86
00:05:28,071 --> 00:05:29,656
as acutely as ever.

87
00:05:29,656 --> 00:05:34,035
Feelings too strong for even
Prome O to purge.

88
00:05:34,035 --> 00:05:35,870
‐ Do you wish them to be purged?

89
00:05:35,870 --> 00:05:38,915
‐ What difference
does that make?

90
00:05:38,915 --> 00:05:42,168
Promise me that
you won't die again.

91
00:05:42,168 --> 00:05:43,544
‐ I'll do my best.

92
00:05:43,544 --> 00:05:45,922
‐ I can't take this,
not knowing what

93
00:05:45,922 --> 00:05:50,093
my emotions might provoke me
to say or do.

94
00:05:50,093 --> 00:05:51,177
[gasps]

95
00:05:51,177 --> 00:05:52,220
‐ And yet, they must have

96
00:05:52,220 --> 00:05:53,596
served some purpose.

97
00:05:53,596 --> 00:05:55,890
Age and Bellcross
relied on them.

98
00:05:55,890 --> 00:05:58,768
Perhaps you may come
to do the same.

99
00:05:58,768 --> 00:06:00,561
‐ Should I seek Age's help?

100
00:06:00,561 --> 00:06:04,899
I am the only one left who has
yet to speak with the fifth.

101
00:06:05,942 --> 00:06:09,028
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

102
00:06:09,028 --> 00:06:13,950
<i>♪ ♪</i>

103
00:06:13,950 --> 00:06:15,618
‐ Stupid monkey.

104
00:06:15,618 --> 00:06:17,578
I was supposed to take you
back home with me.

105
00:06:17,578 --> 00:06:19,247
I made you a promise, remember?

106
00:06:19,247 --> 00:06:22,375
‐ He probably just went ahead
to make it safe for us.

107
00:06:22,375 --> 00:06:25,128
‐ He'd do that.
You think that's what he did.

108
00:06:25,128 --> 00:06:26,546
Don't you, Mehitak?

109
00:06:26,546 --> 00:06:28,923
‐ Perhaps, but I don't know.

110
00:06:28,923 --> 00:06:31,676
‐ I did sense something
strange within him.

111
00:06:31,676 --> 00:06:34,470
That he and Bellcross
were some sort of key.

112
00:06:34,470 --> 00:06:36,931
I think they and the portal
became as one.

113
00:06:36,931 --> 00:06:39,642
Beyond that,
I'm afraid it is unclear

114
00:06:39,642 --> 00:06:41,936
in what sense
they may have survived.

115
00:06:41,936 --> 00:06:43,980
‐ But the door
must go both ways.

116
00:06:43,980 --> 00:06:48,359
‐ That means Age might be able
to come back to us, right?

117
00:06:48,359 --> 00:06:50,111
MEHITAK: I'm not so sure.

118
00:06:50,111 --> 00:06:52,613
I believe he's waiting for us
on the other side.

119
00:06:52,613 --> 00:06:55,616
That if we were to step through
that door, he'd be there.

120
00:06:55,616 --> 00:06:57,452
‐ Mm.
‐ You're right.

121
00:06:57,452 --> 00:06:58,870
That has to be it.

122
00:06:58,870 --> 00:07:00,538
YUTY: There is only
one way to learn.

123
00:07:00,538 --> 00:07:03,291
Prome O and the others
will arrive shortly.

124
00:07:03,291 --> 00:07:05,168
We have agreed to usher
the Bronze Tribe

125
00:07:05,168 --> 00:07:09,130
through the portal as a sign
of our good faith.

126
00:07:09,130 --> 00:07:11,007
Our contracts are fulfilled.

127
00:07:11,007 --> 00:07:13,051
I've come only
to ask your intentions

128
00:07:13,051 --> 00:07:15,344
on behalf of
your former masters.

129
00:07:15,344 --> 00:07:17,764
‐ I wish to confer again
with Prome O.

130
00:07:17,764 --> 00:07:20,600
Her wisdom is vast,
and I've much to learn.

131
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:23,978
Then I will gladly
step through the portal.

132
00:07:23,978 --> 00:07:25,563
‐ I will go as well.

133
00:07:25,563 --> 00:07:27,899
Beyond that door
lies Age's vision.

134
00:07:27,899 --> 00:07:29,859
‐ Mm‐hmm.
‐ Hmm.

135
00:07:29,859 --> 00:07:32,487
‐ It's certainly compelling.

136
00:07:32,487 --> 00:07:36,282
‐ What about all your talk
of what's important?

137
00:07:36,282 --> 00:07:38,493
‐ I meant every word.

138
00:07:38,493 --> 00:07:39,535
‐ [sighs]

139
00:07:39,535 --> 00:07:41,704
‐ And what of the Iron Tribe?

140
00:07:41,704 --> 00:07:42,997
BOTH: Well...

141
00:07:42,997 --> 00:07:45,458
‐ The oath we swore to Age
still stands.

142
00:07:45,458 --> 00:07:48,336
Though he gave his life to us,
he asked only one thing.

143
00:07:48,336 --> 00:07:52,173
We cannot set out on this
journey until it's done.

144
00:07:52,173 --> 00:07:55,176
It's the least we can do
for our fallen savior.

145
00:07:55,176 --> 00:08:00,014
<i>♪ ♪</i>

146
00:08:00,014 --> 00:08:01,516
‐ [sighs]

147
00:08:01,516 --> 00:08:03,309
<i>♪ ♪</i>

148
00:08:03,309 --> 00:08:06,521
Kita, Fuuto's favorite food.

149
00:08:06,521 --> 00:08:08,189
The roots from postos.

150
00:08:08,189 --> 00:08:09,607
‐ Very well, then.

151
00:08:09,607 --> 00:08:11,359
That'll be the first plant
we cultivate.

152
00:08:11,359 --> 00:08:14,362
With our bare hands, if need be.

153
00:08:14,362 --> 00:08:17,907
‐ Hmm.

154
00:08:17,907 --> 00:08:20,326
Aneasha, have they arrived?

155
00:08:20,326 --> 00:08:22,370
‐ The renovations
in the Imperial Hall

156
00:08:22,370 --> 00:08:25,873
have already been completed,
your highness.

157
00:08:25,873 --> 00:08:28,042
‐ Then in the spirit
of our new friendship,

158
00:08:28,042 --> 00:08:29,877
let us all go bid them welcome.

159
00:08:29,877 --> 00:08:31,963
Before them lay a voyage
the likes of which

160
00:08:31,963 --> 00:08:33,840
we can scarcely fathom.

161
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:36,884
[ships whooshing]

162
00:08:42,807 --> 00:08:45,351
PROME: Your vision has led
the Iron Tribe,

163
00:08:45,351 --> 00:08:47,520
indeed all races, to the truth.

164
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:49,689
We embrace the honor
of your alliance

165
00:08:49,689 --> 00:08:51,858
as equals on the same path.

166
00:08:51,858 --> 00:08:54,610
‐ My dear friend,
we are not yet prepared

167
00:08:54,610 --> 00:08:56,571
to embark on this journey.

168
00:08:56,571 --> 00:08:58,239
‐ But if this is
the place from whence

169
00:08:58,239 --> 00:09:01,075
the Golden Tribe first emerged
into the universe,

170
00:09:01,075 --> 00:09:03,202
and the planet Olone
is the gateway

171
00:09:03,202 --> 00:09:04,787
through which
they passed from it,

172
00:09:04,787 --> 00:09:07,790
has not their prophecy come
full circle in you?

173
00:09:07,790 --> 00:09:09,750
What remains for the Iron Tribe?

174
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:12,253
‐ To guide the stars
as they have guided us.

175
00:09:12,253 --> 00:09:14,630
For I believe
at the heart of that truth

176
00:09:14,630 --> 00:09:17,425
dwells the power
to create new worlds.

177
00:09:17,425 --> 00:09:20,761
Nurture it, and the scales
shall drop from our eyes.

178
00:09:20,761 --> 00:09:24,056
The will of time unfurl
before us as a scroll.

179
00:09:24,056 --> 00:09:27,810
Until that happens, we have not
fulfilled our destiny.

180
00:09:27,810 --> 00:09:30,938
PROME: Through your guidance,
may enlightenment thrive.

181
00:09:30,938 --> 00:09:33,441
No doubt will the door
through which the Silver Tribe

182
00:09:33,441 --> 00:09:34,775
now follows its destiny

183
00:09:34,775 --> 00:09:37,111
open to you once again
when the time is right.

184
00:09:37,111 --> 00:09:40,114
‐ The connections we forge
among diverse Starways

185
00:09:40,114 --> 00:09:42,158
is the momentum
that shall reopen it.

186
00:09:42,158 --> 00:09:44,118
In the end, I believe
if there ever was

187
00:09:44,118 --> 00:09:45,745
a purpose behind our war...

188
00:09:45,745 --> 00:09:48,623
‐ It was to proliferate Starways
throughout the universe.

189
00:09:48,623 --> 00:09:52,126
And Nodos were the instruments
of that purpose.

190
00:09:52,126 --> 00:09:54,670
So that the Iron Tribe
may meet its destiny

191
00:09:54,670 --> 00:09:57,298
with every resource,
the Silver Tribe

192
00:09:57,298 --> 00:10:00,134
hereby makes a gift to you
of our power.

193
00:10:00,134 --> 00:10:01,802
DHIANEILA: Power?

194
00:10:01,802 --> 00:10:04,472
[shimmering]

195
00:10:06,474 --> 00:10:07,391
[gasps]

196
00:10:07,391 --> 00:10:08,601
‐ Before you are the means

197
00:10:08,601 --> 00:10:10,436
with which to govern
this universe.

198
00:10:10,436 --> 00:10:13,481
This will also serve to restore
the lost spiritual link

199
00:10:13,481 --> 00:10:16,108
between you and your former
enemies, the Bronze Tribe.

200
00:10:16,108 --> 00:10:18,611
I leave it to you
to lead those among them

201
00:10:18,611 --> 00:10:20,488
who will remain
once we've gone.

202
00:10:20,488 --> 00:10:22,323
‐ Are you sure, Prome?

203
00:10:22,323 --> 00:10:25,159
‐ A Hedron shield and rule
over the Bronze Tribe.

204
00:10:25,159 --> 00:10:27,537
‐ It would make the princess
all‐powerful.

205
00:10:27,537 --> 00:10:29,497
‐ Oh, Dhianeila.

206
00:10:29,497 --> 00:10:31,332
It's so much to take on.

207
00:10:31,332 --> 00:10:32,959
DHIANEILA: Am I allowed to share
the burden

208
00:10:32,959 --> 00:10:35,545
of this responsibility
with the other tribes?

209
00:10:35,545 --> 00:10:40,424
PROME: If by your lights,
you deem them ready, you are.

210
00:10:42,009 --> 00:10:44,512
‐ Then I accept your gifts,
Prome O.

211
00:10:44,512 --> 00:10:47,306
And with them, the sacred
weight of emotion

212
00:10:47,306 --> 00:10:50,476
which you alone
once had to bear.

213
00:10:50,476 --> 00:10:52,186
‐ May it serve you well.

214
00:10:52,186 --> 00:10:55,648
<i>[swelling orchestral music]</i>

215
00:10:55,648 --> 00:10:57,024
‐ Hmm.

216
00:10:57,024 --> 00:11:00,111
<i>♪ ♪</i>

217
00:11:00,111 --> 00:11:03,614
‐ The time has arrived.
We Nodos must step through.

218
00:11:03,614 --> 00:11:07,368
And if your paths do cross his,
the fifth will return to you

219
00:11:07,368 --> 00:11:11,747
with all of our powers
in his possession.

220
00:11:11,747 --> 00:11:14,375
‐ Words can't express
how grateful I am.

221
00:11:14,375 --> 00:11:15,960
We are in your debt.

222
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:17,878
I thank you, Yuty La.

223
00:11:17,878 --> 00:11:23,217
<i>♪ ♪</i>

224
00:11:23,217 --> 00:11:25,219
‐ Do they really call us?

225
00:11:25,219 --> 00:11:26,804
Or shall we reach
the other side,

226
00:11:26,804 --> 00:11:29,765
only to find they have left us
once again?

227
00:11:29,765 --> 00:11:32,727
Is the dream we hold
a foolish one?

228
00:11:32,727 --> 00:11:34,437
‐ Come now, Rom Ror.

229
00:11:34,437 --> 00:11:36,230
In this bold, new age,

230
00:11:36,230 --> 00:11:38,065
we may dream as we will.

231
00:11:38,065 --> 00:11:45,114
<i>♪ ♪</i>

232
00:11:50,911 --> 00:11:53,998
[engines blasting]

233
00:11:55,041 --> 00:11:57,918
[shattering]

234
00:11:57,918 --> 00:12:00,004
MOBEEDO: Imagine our being
able to launch

235
00:12:00,004 --> 00:12:01,756
without consuming energy.

236
00:12:01,756 --> 00:12:03,924
A thank‐you hardly
seems sufficient

237
00:12:03,924 --> 00:12:05,676
after all you've done for us.

238
00:12:05,676 --> 00:12:09,055
PHAETHO: Hmm, will this heap
be able to keep up?

239
00:12:09,055 --> 00:12:11,098
‐ [laughs]
I don't know.

240
00:12:11,098 --> 00:12:15,853
This heap certainly held its own
when you were attacking it.

241
00:12:15,853 --> 00:12:19,357
‐ Now it seems it's your turn
to shadow us.

242
00:12:19,357 --> 00:12:22,443
‐ Safe journey, friend.

243
00:12:34,163 --> 00:12:37,249
[shimmering blast]

244
00:12:38,834 --> 00:12:40,961
NILVAL: I'll give the Silver
Tribe this much:

245
00:12:40,961 --> 00:12:43,547
they sure know how
to assemble a fleet.

246
00:12:43,547 --> 00:12:45,299
‐ Well, aren't you
the lucky one?

247
00:12:45,299 --> 00:12:48,969
Seeing our new friends off as
they bid this universe farewell.

248
00:12:48,969 --> 00:12:52,515
Who can say when we'll go
through that door ourselves?

249
00:12:52,515 --> 00:12:54,392
‐ [gasps]

250
00:12:54,392 --> 00:12:57,812
Who can say, indeed.

251
00:12:57,812 --> 00:12:59,647
PROME: There is no way of
knowing what lay

252
00:12:59,647 --> 00:13:01,816
on the other side until
we have crossed over.

253
00:13:01,816 --> 00:13:03,984
But I believe that you and I
both possess

254
00:13:03,984 --> 00:13:07,154
more than an inkling
of what awaits, do we not?

255
00:13:07,154 --> 00:13:10,282
DHIANEILA: The mysteries of the
future are often overshadowed

256
00:13:10,282 --> 00:13:12,243
by the mysteries of the present.

257
00:13:12,243 --> 00:13:14,578
We can only wait and see.

258
00:13:14,578 --> 00:13:16,288
‐ Spoken like a true sage.

259
00:13:16,288 --> 00:13:19,166
May the wisdom of the stars
forever light your way.

260
00:13:19,166 --> 00:13:21,502
‐ And so may they shine
down on you.

261
00:13:21,502 --> 00:13:25,005
That the path before your people
be an easy one.

262
00:13:25,005 --> 00:13:28,050
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

263
00:13:28,050 --> 00:13:35,099
<i>♪ ♪</i>

264
00:13:52,825 --> 00:14:00,708
<i>♪ ♪</i>

265
00:14:00,708 --> 00:14:02,209
[explosion]

266
00:14:02,209 --> 00:14:09,258
<i>♪ ♪</i>

267
00:14:25,316 --> 00:14:31,405
<i>♪ ♪</i>

268
00:14:31,405 --> 00:14:33,407
‐ We'll never see Age again.

269
00:14:33,407 --> 00:14:35,743
‐ No, he'll come back someday.

270
00:14:35,743 --> 00:14:37,286
You'll see.

271
00:14:37,286 --> 00:14:40,247
‐ I hope you're right.

272
00:14:40,247 --> 00:14:41,749
AGE: The future waits,
Dhianeila.

273
00:14:41,749 --> 00:14:43,375
‐ [gasps]

274
00:14:43,375 --> 00:14:47,129
‐ Before you lay the path.

275
00:14:47,129 --> 00:14:48,631
‐ [gasps]

276
00:14:48,631 --> 00:14:53,093
<i>♪ ♪</i>

277
00:14:53,093 --> 00:14:54,386
Yes, Age.

278
00:14:54,386 --> 00:14:55,763
I understand.

279
00:14:55,763 --> 00:14:58,390
‐ Are you feeling all right?

280
00:14:58,390 --> 00:14:59,767
DHIANEILA: Let us go.

281
00:14:59,767 --> 00:15:02,436
Until the doorway deems us worth
to reopen it,

282
00:15:02,436 --> 00:15:04,813
this planet must serve
as a beacon of hope

283
00:15:04,813 --> 00:15:06,524
to tribes everywhere.

284
00:15:06,524 --> 00:15:09,568
Our goal is to spread that hope
across the universe

285
00:15:09,568 --> 00:15:12,446
so that all tribes
may soon know freedom.

286
00:15:12,446 --> 00:15:14,698
<i>♪ ♪</i>

287
00:15:14,698 --> 00:15:17,451
Long, long ago,

288
00:15:17,451 --> 00:15:20,621
in a time all but lost
to memory,

289
00:15:20,621 --> 00:15:24,250
the words of the Golden Tribe
echoed through the void.

290
00:15:24,250 --> 00:15:28,045
And three great tribes
there were who heeded them,

291
00:15:28,045 --> 00:15:30,005
summoned by that call.

292
00:15:30,005 --> 00:15:32,466
The Silver Tribe,

293
00:15:32,466 --> 00:15:34,802
the Bronze Tribe,

294
00:15:34,802 --> 00:15:37,763
and the Heroic Tribe
each set out in turn

295
00:15:37,763 --> 00:15:39,390
to bask in the wide universe

296
00:15:39,390 --> 00:15:42,142
beyond those worlds
which had cradled them.

297
00:15:42,142 --> 00:15:45,854
Later, when in their boundless
wisdom the Golden Tribe chose

298
00:15:45,854 --> 00:15:48,482
to leave this universe
for another,

299
00:15:48,482 --> 00:15:51,819
a new people emerged
to answer their call.

300
00:15:51,819 --> 00:15:54,154
Upon these people
was bestowed a name

301
00:15:54,154 --> 00:15:57,658
befitting their spirit,
the Iron Tribe.

302
00:15:57,658 --> 00:16:00,744
And they, encountering
hardships untested,

303
00:16:00,744 --> 00:16:04,373
conquering obstacles untold
through journeys uncharted,

304
00:16:04,373 --> 00:16:06,625
inspired the very stars
themselves

305
00:16:06,625 --> 00:16:10,629
to bejewel the universe
in peace and wisdom.

306
00:16:10,629 --> 00:16:13,799
But believing that a still
greater destiny

307
00:16:13,799 --> 00:16:16,176
lay ahead of them,
the Iron Tribe

308
00:16:16,176 --> 00:16:19,763
quietly yearned to stand
alongside their forbearers

309
00:16:19,763 --> 00:16:22,850
in the Great Beyond.

310
00:16:22,850 --> 00:16:25,811
And for that honor, waited.

311
00:16:25,811 --> 00:16:32,818
<i>♪ ♪</i>

312
00:16:40,159 --> 00:16:41,994
‐ It's beautiful.

313
00:16:41,994 --> 00:16:45,039
<i>[whimsical orchestral music]</i>

314
00:16:45,039 --> 00:16:48,042
[mechanical whirring]

315
00:16:48,042 --> 00:16:54,131
<i>♪ ♪</i>

316
00:16:54,131 --> 00:16:56,508
‐ I'm finally going to make good
on my promise to you.

317
00:16:56,508 --> 00:16:58,761
‐ I'm surprised you hadn't
forgotten it altogether.

318
00:16:58,761 --> 00:17:01,347
‐ Hey, I told you my word
was my bond, didn't I?

319
00:17:01,347 --> 00:17:04,391
‐ Well, your bond took two
cycles to come through.

320
00:17:04,391 --> 00:17:06,352
‐ Ah...
The twins should be

321
00:17:06,352 --> 00:17:08,562
arriving at the location
shortly.

322
00:17:08,562 --> 00:17:09,730
How are you holding up?

323
00:17:09,730 --> 00:17:12,066
‐ Quite well,
thank you very much.

324
00:17:12,066 --> 00:17:15,861
<i>♪ ♪</i>

325
00:17:18,072 --> 00:17:19,698
‐ Well, now, look who's arguing

326
00:17:19,698 --> 00:17:22,201
and ignoring what the princess
asked them to do.

327
00:17:22,201 --> 00:17:23,577
‐ We're going
to have to punish you

328
00:17:23,577 --> 00:17:25,954
if you can't learn
how to behave.

329
00:17:25,954 --> 00:17:28,207
BOTH: Ah...

330
00:17:28,207 --> 00:17:30,542
Ha!

331
00:17:30,542 --> 00:17:32,962
Hmm!

332
00:17:35,798 --> 00:17:38,258
NILVAL: I suppose even the best
and brightest among us

333
00:17:38,258 --> 00:17:40,928
are no match for
the Unos Knights.

334
00:17:40,928 --> 00:17:43,138
‐ Be that as it may,
they're the only unit

335
00:17:43,138 --> 00:17:45,724
that's permitted to use
a Hedron shield.

336
00:17:45,724 --> 00:17:47,935
‐ Our sister Dhianeila
is the undisputed

337
00:17:47,935 --> 00:17:50,521
leader of all three peoples
in the known universe.

338
00:17:50,521 --> 00:17:53,399
‐ On behalf of her name,
we cannot afford to spare

339
00:17:53,399 --> 00:17:57,069
any measure in consolidating
the power of the Iron Tribe.

340
00:17:57,069 --> 00:17:58,529
‐ Some things never change.

341
00:17:58,529 --> 00:18:00,280
They still ride
their sister's coattails

342
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:01,865
like a couple of idiots.

343
00:18:01,865 --> 00:18:03,659
‐ It looks like the Knights
unit, Captain,

344
00:18:03,659 --> 00:18:05,327
and the others have arrived.

345
00:18:05,327 --> 00:18:06,996
MAN: To step through
to the great beyond!

346
00:18:06,996 --> 00:18:08,747
‐ May I express
my heartfelt gratitude

347
00:18:08,747 --> 00:18:11,458
to Grand Duchess Nilval
for generously allowing us

348
00:18:11,458 --> 00:18:13,585
the priority use
of Earth Starway.

349
00:18:13,585 --> 00:18:14,920
We're forever in your debt.

350
00:18:14,920 --> 00:18:16,255
NILVAL: Don't mention it.

351
00:18:16,255 --> 00:18:17,798
After all, if not for your
intercession,

352
00:18:17,798 --> 00:18:20,634
we might have had another
war on our hands.

353
00:18:20,634 --> 00:18:22,469
I'm not positive
that's a concession

354
00:18:22,469 --> 00:18:24,138
a grand duchess should make,
but as far

355
00:18:24,138 --> 00:18:26,056
as I'm concerned,
it's the God's truth.

356
00:18:26,056 --> 00:18:27,641
Besides, I'm no good at this.

357
00:18:27,641 --> 00:18:29,226
‐ And yet, your rule
of this system

358
00:18:29,226 --> 00:18:30,769
has been unparalleled.

359
00:18:30,769 --> 00:18:32,646
‐ Oh, I'm just a glorified
crossing guard

360
00:18:32,646 --> 00:18:34,440
for ships en route to Earth,
really.

361
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:36,525
To be perfectly honest,
I'd much prefer

362
00:18:36,525 --> 00:18:39,194
to wield a Hedron shield
as proper warriors do.

363
00:18:39,194 --> 00:18:41,155
‐ Then you will be pleased
to know that the princess

364
00:18:41,155 --> 00:18:44,283
intends for all of us to
brandish such powers one day.

365
00:18:44,283 --> 00:18:47,745
Her vision of the future has its
foundations in that very thing.

366
00:18:47,745 --> 00:18:49,955
‐ A fine thought.
For the sake of the universe,

367
00:18:49,955 --> 00:18:51,999
I hope she's successful.

368
00:18:51,999 --> 00:18:53,667
And please, send my regards.

369
00:18:53,667 --> 00:18:56,003
It's a shame she couldn't come
visit us herself.

370
00:18:56,003 --> 00:18:57,671
‐ She offers her regrets,
but she has

371
00:18:57,671 --> 00:18:59,923
pressing business on Olone.

372
00:18:59,923 --> 00:19:01,675
‐ So I hear.

373
00:19:01,675 --> 00:19:03,510
WOMAN:
It's the slowest‐rotating planet

374
00:19:03,510 --> 00:19:05,637
in its system
by a full half‐cycle.

375
00:19:05,637 --> 00:19:08,682
That has much to do with why
the project has taken so long.

376
00:19:08,682 --> 00:19:10,350
BEE NO BEE: The ecological
vital scan

377
00:19:10,350 --> 00:19:12,770
is being conducted
on schedule, Master.

378
00:19:12,770 --> 00:19:14,521
MOBEEDO: Where's the princess?

379
00:19:14,521 --> 00:19:15,856
BEE NO BEE: Surveying the land.

380
00:19:15,856 --> 00:19:19,485
She's currently in sector
N3009‐E049.

381
00:19:19,485 --> 00:19:20,986
‐ Hmm.

382
00:19:20,986 --> 00:19:22,696
Call her on the psych line, Bee.

383
00:19:26,533 --> 00:19:29,536
<i>[dramatic piano music]</i>

384
00:19:29,536 --> 00:19:36,585
<i>♪ ♪</i>

385
00:19:38,045 --> 00:19:41,048
[chittering]

386
00:19:42,216 --> 00:19:44,384
[woman singing in Japanese]

387
00:19:44,384 --> 00:19:45,928
MOBEEDO: Your highness,
the planet's

388
00:19:45,928 --> 00:19:47,971
eco vital signs
appear to check out.

389
00:19:47,971 --> 00:19:50,015
DHIANEILA: Would you mind
if I stay down here?

390
00:19:50,015 --> 00:19:51,558
Just a little while longer.

391
00:19:51,558 --> 00:19:53,185
MOBEEDO: Not at all, Princess.

392
00:19:53,185 --> 00:19:55,854
Oh, by the way, the council
just passed a motion

393
00:19:55,854 --> 00:19:58,816
to have a monument erected
on the planet's surface.

394
00:19:58,816 --> 00:20:00,150
DHIANEILA: A monument?

395
00:20:00,150 --> 00:20:02,361
MOBEEDO: To commemorate Age,
your highness.

396
00:20:02,361 --> 00:20:04,488
This was once his home,
after all.

397
00:20:04,488 --> 00:20:06,156
DHIANEILA: There's no need,
Captain.

398
00:20:06,156 --> 00:20:09,409
The fate of Age's legacy rests
in hands not our own.

399
00:20:09,409 --> 00:20:11,286
MOBEEDO: Whose, then?

400
00:20:11,286 --> 00:20:14,581
<i>♪ ♪</i>

401
00:20:14,581 --> 00:20:16,416
DHIANEILA: When these
magnificent creatures

402
00:20:16,416 --> 00:20:18,710
take the first step
toward civilization,

403
00:20:18,710 --> 00:20:20,504
I have no doubt that Age's name

404
00:20:20,504 --> 00:20:22,214
will be passed down
through generations

405
00:20:22,214 --> 00:20:23,590
in a language more beautiful

406
00:20:23,590 --> 00:20:25,759
than anything wrought
by humankind.

407
00:20:25,759 --> 00:20:27,553
‐ I am sure you're right.

408
00:20:27,553 --> 00:20:29,805
There's still a few things
that need to be done

409
00:20:29,805 --> 00:20:31,890
before we take off,
so feel free

410
00:20:31,890 --> 00:20:33,559
to stay as long as you want.

411
00:20:33,559 --> 00:20:35,811
DHIANEILA: Thank you, Captain.

412
00:20:35,811 --> 00:20:38,939
‐ But Master, we're already
prepared to take off.

413
00:20:38,939 --> 00:20:40,357
‐ Shut up, idiot.

414
00:20:40,357 --> 00:20:42,776
I said that so she could have
some time alone.

415
00:20:42,776 --> 00:20:44,319
‐ But that's an egregious breach

416
00:20:44,319 --> 00:20:46,446
of our security protocol,
Master.

417
00:20:46,446 --> 00:20:49,533
‐ Take my word for it: there's
not a thing in the universe

418
00:20:49,533 --> 00:20:51,118
that can hurt her down there.

419
00:20:51,118 --> 00:20:53,245
You may not understand it,
but it's actually

420
00:20:53,245 --> 00:20:55,038
she who is protecting us.

421
00:20:55,038 --> 00:20:59,126
So be patient, and let her say
good‐bye to planet Olone.

422
00:20:59,126 --> 00:21:01,420
With all the memories
it holds for her,

423
00:21:01,420 --> 00:21:04,882
it's a wonder she can
leave it at all.

424
00:21:04,882 --> 00:21:06,675
<i>♪ ♪</i>

425
00:21:06,675 --> 00:21:09,678
[woman singing in Japanese]

426
00:21:09,678 --> 00:21:12,639
DHIANEILA: You lived here
by yourself for so long.

427
00:21:12,639 --> 00:21:16,268
Somehow, I know you weren't
lonely, though.

428
00:21:16,268 --> 00:21:18,270
Not really.

429
00:21:18,270 --> 00:21:21,899
I used to think it was because
you'd been shown the future,

430
00:21:21,899 --> 00:21:25,235
because you'd seen that one day,
we would come,

431
00:21:25,235 --> 00:21:27,070
and that you would devote
yourself to something

432
00:21:27,070 --> 00:21:30,490
so much larger than the life
you knew here.

433
00:21:30,490 --> 00:21:33,118
But it was more than that.

434
00:21:33,118 --> 00:21:35,162
No future is set in stone.

435
00:21:35,162 --> 00:21:37,789
I understand that now.

436
00:21:37,789 --> 00:21:41,001
It takes faith to accept
destiny as you did.

437
00:21:41,001 --> 00:21:45,839
<i>♪ ♪</i>

438
00:21:45,839 --> 00:21:48,592
Even though this view
is the closest thing I have

439
00:21:48,592 --> 00:21:50,928
to standing beside you,

440
00:21:50,928 --> 00:21:52,971
I have to leave it now.

441
00:21:52,971 --> 00:21:55,849
<i>♪ ♪</i>

442
00:21:55,849 --> 00:21:58,393
For everything that you've done,

443
00:21:58,393 --> 00:22:00,187
thank you.

444
00:22:00,187 --> 00:22:04,983
<i>♪ ♪</i>

445
00:22:04,983 --> 00:22:07,027
Good‐bye, Age.

446
00:22:07,027 --> 00:22:11,240
<i>♪ ♪</i>

447
00:22:11,240 --> 00:22:14,284
[waves crashing]

448
00:22:15,369 --> 00:22:17,704
[alarm blaring]
‐ Huh? By the gods!

449
00:22:17,704 --> 00:22:20,874
‐ A massive temporal shift has
been detected, Master.

450
00:22:20,874 --> 00:22:23,335
WOMAN: An unexplained energy
field has been confirmed

451
00:22:23,335 --> 00:22:25,796
interfering with the planet's
axial tilt.

452
00:22:25,796 --> 00:22:27,547
Whatever it is, it's huge.

453
00:22:27,547 --> 00:22:29,883
‐ Huh?
Unknown?

454
00:22:29,883 --> 00:22:33,345
Just what the hell
is going on down there?

455
00:22:33,345 --> 00:22:35,889
Hold on. Bee, look at that.

456
00:22:35,889 --> 00:22:37,766
This isn't a temporal shift.

457
00:22:37,766 --> 00:22:40,852
Olone's realigning itself
to its original orbit.

458
00:22:40,852 --> 00:22:44,314
<i>[eerie music]</i>

459
00:22:44,314 --> 00:22:46,191
[wind blowing]

460
00:22:55,742 --> 00:22:57,786
‐ [gasps]

461
00:22:59,162 --> 00:23:02,207
[explosion]

462
00:23:05,460 --> 00:23:07,587
It's another portal.

463
00:23:07,587 --> 00:23:10,299
Just like Elysium.

464
00:23:10,299 --> 00:23:12,759
Am I dreaming?

465
00:23:12,759 --> 00:23:15,804
[explosion]

466
00:23:25,105 --> 00:23:27,774
AGE: Dhianeila created a path.

467
00:23:27,774 --> 00:23:30,819
<i>[dramatic piano music]</i>

468
00:23:30,819 --> 00:23:37,868
<i>♪ ♪</i>

469
00:23:48,211 --> 00:23:49,463
‐ [gasps]

470
00:23:49,463 --> 00:23:52,674
[sobbing]

471
00:23:52,674 --> 00:23:59,723
<i>♪ ♪</i>

472
00:24:02,309 --> 00:24:04,102
[woman singing in Japanese]

473
00:24:04,102 --> 00:24:06,104
‐ Age!

474
00:24:06,104 --> 00:24:08,440
[grunting]

475
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:15,155
<i>♪ ♪</i>

476
00:24:15,155 --> 00:24:16,990
[panting]

477
00:24:16,990 --> 00:24:24,039
<i>♪ ♪</i>

